title: Individual Deposits, National Banks, Country Districts for United States
notes:
Monthly Coverage Varies From Year To Year. All Years Have Scattered Five Month Coverage, Except For 1874 Which Has Coverage For Only October And December, And 1914 Which Has Coverage For Six Months. Data For 1874-October 1914 Were Computed From The Sum Of Unpaid Dividends And Individual Deposits. Data For October And December 1914 Are The Summed Figures For Dividends Unpaid For All Fifty States As No Composite Figure Was Given. Source: Annual Reports Of The Comptroller Of The Currency.

This NBER data series m14022 appears on the NBER website in Chapter 14 at http://www.nber.org/databases/macrohistory/contents/chapter14.html.
